  "optimization_hints": [
    "Q1: Full scan lineitem (60M rows), 4-row GROUP BY. Use sorted agg if pre-sorted on (returnflag,linestatus), else hash agg with SIMD sum.",
    "Q2: Selective PK lookup. Build hash index on part(type,size). Correlated subquery → semi-join reduction with zone maps.",
    "Q3: Star join (customer-orders-lineitem), selective date filters. Use hash join customer→orders→lineitem; apply filters early.",
    "Q4: Filtered scan orders with semi-join EXISTS. Bloom filter on lineitem commit/receipt dates to prune orders.",
    "Q5: Multi-way join through region/nation. Pre-aggregate at lineitem level, push region filter early. Consider materialized temp table.",
    "Q6: Simple range scan on lineitem with AND predicates. Zone-map skip on l_shipdate+l_discount. Vectorized counting.",
    "Q7: Two-year range scan → 2-pass aggregation. Pre-filter nation pairs, hash partition by (supp_nation,cust_nation).",
    "Q8: Selective subquery with CASE. Use semi-join for part type, partial aggregation at 2-phase level.",
    "Q9: Four-way join (part-supplier-lineitem-partsupp) with LIKE. Hash partitioning, operator fusion to avoid materialization.",
    "Q10: Selective date range + returnflag='R'. Build hash index on orders(orderdate), semi-join on lineitem.",
    "Q11: GROUP BY all partkeys on partsupp. Use hash agg with HAVING filter. Consider two-phase agg if HAVING is selective.",
    "Q12: Hash join orders-lineitem with shipmode IN list. Build multi-value hash index on l_shipmode.",
    "Q13: LEFT OUTER JOIN with comment predicate. Hash agg on result; handle NULL groups explicitly.",
    "Q14: Simple filter + CASE aggregation. Operator fusion (scan-filter-project-agg). Vectorized LIKE matching.",
    "Q15: CTE (revenue0) as window function. Hash agg l_suppkey, then max() reduction. Consider sorted agg if pre-sorted.",
    "Q16: GROUP BY (brand,type,size) with COUNT(DISTINCT suppkey). Hash agg with distinct tracking; IN subquery → bloom filter.",
    "Q17: Correlated scalar subquery (avg per partkey). Decorrelate to two-pass: compute avg per part, then filter in join.",
    "Q18: Large IN subquery (orderkey with qty>300). Semi-join → hash table of qualifying orderkeys, probe lineitem.",
    "Q19: Complex OR disjunction on (brand,container,size,quantity). Rewrite as UNION for independent hash agg per branch.",
    "Q20: Double-nested subquery. Flatten: partsupp→part name filter→ps_availqty calc vs lineitem aggregate. Hash join with HAVING.",
    "Q21: EXISTS + NOT EXISTS subqueries with self-join on lineitem. Rewrite as anti-join + semi-join; multi-way hash join.",
    "Q22: Substring predicate (phone country code) + scalar subquery (avg balance). Use zone maps on c_acctbal; vectorize SUBSTRING."
  ],
  "summary": "TPC-H SF10 workload is dominated by fact-table scans (lineitem 60M, orders 15M) with selective filtering on date/amount columns and multi-way dimension joins. Q1 and Q6 are full-scan aggregations with 4-7 result groups; Q3, Q5, Q7, Q9 involve complex multi-table star joins with early filters; Q16 and Q15 are GROUP BY cardinality-heavy. Bottlenecks: (1) 60M lineitem scans repeated across Q1,Q3,Q5,Q6,Q7,Q8,Q9,Q12,Q14 require zone-map pruning and SIMD filtering; (2) correlated subqueries in Q2,Q11,Q15,Q17,Q20,Q22 need decorrelation and semi-join optimization; (3) multi-way joins (5-7 tables) require careful ordering (region→nation→customer/supplier first) and hash partitioning. Key optimizations: vectorized scans with zone-map skip, hash aggregation for medium-cardinality groups, semi-join reduction for subqueries, parallel hash join with 64-core thread pool using morsel-driven parallelism (10K-100K row chunks)."
}
